text: Ebner-Free House was a historic home located at Vincennes, Knox County, Indiana. It was built in 1887, and was a 2 1/2-story, frame dwelling with Eastlake Movement ornamentation. Note: This includes and Accompanying photographs. It has been demolished. It was added to the National Register of Historic Places in 1985 and delisted in 1999. ==References== Category:Former National Register of Historic Places in Indiana Category:Vincennes, Indiana Category:Houses on the National Register of Historic Places in Indiana Category:Houses completed in 1887 Category:Buildings and structures in Knox County, Indiana Category:National Register of Historic Places in Knox County, Indiana
title: Ebner-Free House
